Definition: a law stating that mechanical work can be derived from a body only when that body interacts with another at a lower temperature
Example: any spontaneous process results in an increase of entropy
Synonyms: law_of_thermodynamics, a, law, stating, that, mechanical, work, can, be, derived, from, body, only, when, interacts, with, another, at, lower, temperature, any, spontaneous, process, results, in, an, increase, of, entropy
Category: noun.cognition
